---

<section class="section" id="acct-cashflow-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Cash flow management, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-cashflow-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Cash flow management, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <p class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</p>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-cashflow-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">When cash flow management earns its keep</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is yes.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Most owners reach for active cash management when one of these starts keeping them up at night.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-cashflow-delivers">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What&rsquo;s included</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What cash flow management actually delivers.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Scoped to your business and updated on a rhythm that matches how fast your cash moves.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for d in deliverables %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ d.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-cashflow-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From first forecast to a number you trust.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every cash flow engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; built on books that are accurate first.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-cashflow-beyond">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Beyond the forecast</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">When cash is under control, the bigger questions open up.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A reliable forecast does more than prevent shortfalls &mdash; it changes what you can plan. Once you can see cash clearly, you can decide when to hire, whether to expand, how to price for margin, and how much you can safely invest in growth. That&rsquo;s the natural step from managing cash to steering the business.</p>
      <p>For businesses that want that judgment on an ongoing basis, a <strong>fractional CFO</strong> takes cash management as one piece of a broader seat &mdash; forecasting, KPIs, strategy, and board-level reporting. As automation handles the routine, this is where the real value now lives. <a href="/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/?intent=fractional-cfo">Explore fractional CFO &amp; advisory &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-cashflow-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Cash flow management questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acct-cashflow-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="acct-cashflow-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-cashflow-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot delivers cash flow management. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for accuracy on forecasting method, working-capital management, and the boundaries of the service. Where our approach or scope changes, this page is updated. Cash flow management is delivered on accurate books and coordinated with your banker and CPA for anything requiring a license.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source">Page last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-cashflow-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Related advisory &amp; services.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
